Reference adapter connecting the summarizer pipeline to Anthropic's Messages API; this is the default `CTX_AGENT_CMD` target and the only piece of the system that speaks to Claude directly. It is intentionally Python and outside the Rust lint regime, mirroring `prompts/`'s exemption.

The stdin/stdout contract is fixed and must stay in sync with whatever invokes it (the Rust runner): stdin is a single JSON object `{"system": str, "user": str}`, stdout is the model's raw completion text with nothing else appended, and any error goes to stderr with a non-zero exit. The adapter adds no instructions of its own — per `prompts/README.md`'s decoupling rule, `system` is forwarded verbatim as a cache-control-tagged block so repeated leaf/rollup calls in one task hit Anthropic's prompt cache.

Non-obvious behavior: `thinking` is explicitly disabled and `output_config.effort` is forced to `"low"` — this is a deliberate choice for summarization's strict-format, low-intelligence workload, not an oversight. If tasks change to require heavier reasoning, this pinning must be revisited.

Config is entirely env-driven: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (required, dies if absent), `CTX_AGENT_MODEL` (default `claude-sonnet-5`), `CTX_AGENT_MAX_TOKENS` (default 2048), `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` (default `https://api.anthropic.com`). `CTX_AGENT_TEMPERATURE` is documented in the module docstring but not actually read anywhere in the code — dead/unimplemented option.

Key functions: `read_request() -> tuple[str, str]` parses and validates stdin JSON, dying on malformed input or missing/non-string fields. `build_body(system, user) -> dict` assembles the Messages API payload. `call_api(body) -> dict` performs the HTTP POST via `urllib`, dying with formatted messages on HTTP or network errors. `extract_text(response) -> str` concatenates `type == "text"` content blocks, dying on unexpected shape or empty result. `die(message)` is the shared error path (prints to stderr, raises `SystemExit(1)`) — invariant: the process never exits non-zero silently.